result.execSummary:
The defendant Cassie M Edlebeck was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Retail Theft - Intentionally Take >$500 - $5000), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.50(1m)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes:
Restitution:  $350.13 to Roundy's to be paid as a Condition of Probation at the rate of $50.00 per month starting 11-01-2015.

If Probation/Extended Supervision is revoked and/or a prison term ordered, outstanding financial obligations shall be collected pursuant to statutory provisions, including deductions from inmate prison monies.  If discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant and in favor of restitution victims and government entities for outstanding financial obligations.  Collections may include income assignment.

Cost and Surcharge to be paid as a Condition of Probation at the rate of $50.00 per month starting 09-01-2015 and/or 53 hours of Community Service to be completed by the end of Probation.  Failure to pay or complete Community Service the court orders 5 days Huber as Contempt.
AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended.
Mental Health Evaluation and follow through with any treatment recommended.

Defense request expunction.  State objects.

Expunction is conditionally granted upon completion of sentence, payment of all costs/fees/restitution and no new criminal convictions or pending cases.  Defendant must Petition the Court in writing upon successful completion of the sentence.

Maintain ABSOLUTE SOBRIETY.
Submit Random Urine Screens.
No use or possession of alcohol or illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia.
No use or possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription.
Any valid prescription drugs must be taken in the manner in which they are prescribed.
Inform Agent of all prescriptions.
Sign any/all Medical Releases for Agent.
Be involved in a12 step program within 2 weeks of Probation  and obtain a mentor/sponsor.
Attend at least 1 meeting a week.
Within First 60 days obtain a valid driver' license.
Operate a motor vehicle with a valid driver's license.
No contact with Walmart in Delafield and Pick N Save at Pabst Farms.
Provide DNA Sample, if not yet provided and Pay Surcharge.

Case #15CM224 was Dismissed and Read into Case #15CF156.
